 The school celebrated a pass rate of 98.6%, with their top three achievers making an average of over 80%. Their top three achievers are as follows: •The head girl of 2018, Sirisha Bawanideen, passed with seven distinctions and an average of 88%.
•Aaliya Gani came second with three distinctions and an average of 81%.
•Tasneen Gani followed with four distinctions and an average of 80%. The principal of Steelcrest, Ms Ray Eksteen, bids her matriculants farewell with a few parting words, “May your feet leave Steelcrest, but never your heart. Take care and good luck with your future.”   Traffic officers to appear in court for corruption #TrafficAlert: Two dead in Kranspoort accidents VIDEO: Two perish after truck jack-knifes  • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za 